1
00:00:01,710 --> 00:00:03,923
I guess we won't be seeing each other anymore.

2
00:00:12,941 --> 00:00:14,861
Take care of yourself.

3
00:00:33,064 --> 00:00:37,490
Ahh, it always touches my heart no matter how many times I see it.

4
00:00:38,284 --> 00:00:39,744
Thank you for your hard work.

5
00:00:43,627 --> 00:00:45,298
It's an old movie, but...

6
00:00:45,381 --> 00:00:47,760
I wonder if young people like you

7
00:00:47,844 --> 00:00:49,973
were able to enjoy it.

8
00:00:50,224 --> 00:00:51,977
Yes, of course.

9
00:00:52,060 --> 00:00:53,772
It was really interesting.

10
00:00:54,107 --> 00:00:56,236
Mother, how about showing them

11
00:00:56,320 --> 00:00:58,115
the room upstairs as well?

12
00:00:58,324 --> 00:00:59,576
We have small props

13
00:00:59,659 --> 00:01:00,995
that Mother used in her movies on display.

14
00:01:01,078 --> 00:01:03,751
Oh! Then by all means.

15
00:01:04,377 --> 00:01:10,389
♪~♪

16
00:01:17,570 --> 00:01:21,328
The blackness of shadows, the density of darkness—
the light of reasoning cuts right through them.

17
00:01:21,411 --> 00:01:25,127
A fire at a movie star's mansion.
The surprising secret hidden in a painting.

18
00:01:25,211 --> 00:01:26,630
See through the one and only truth.

19
00:01:26,713 --> 00:01:28,425
Looks like a kid, but has the mind of an adult.

20
00:01:28,634 --> 00:01:31,348
His name is Detective Conan!

21
00:02:55,544 --> 00:03:01,556
♪~♪

22
00:03:03,612 --> 00:03:08,712
"A Diamond, Artwork and a Great Actress"

23
00:03:09,531 --> 00:03:12,662
Oh my. Nothing but nostalgic movies.

24
00:03:12,745 --> 00:03:16,335
It's like a little Shirakawa Misuzu memorial museum.

25
00:03:16,418 --> 00:03:17,588
You're embarrassing me.

26
00:03:18,089 --> 00:03:20,636
These are things my late husband collected.

27
00:03:20,719 --> 00:03:21,846
I see.

28
00:03:22,264 --> 00:03:24,644
This is the room where we've organized

29
00:03:24,727 --> 00:03:26,648
the costumes and props from back then.

30
00:03:26,731 --> 00:03:27,817
Oh!

31
00:03:28,569 --> 00:03:31,866
Wow... amazing.

32
00:03:34,747 --> 00:03:36,960
This is Mother's bedroom.

33
00:03:37,168 --> 00:03:39,006
Memorable items and valuable things

34
00:03:39,089 --> 00:03:41,803
are kept in this glass case.

35
00:03:43,139 --> 00:03:45,686
Wow! Is this real?

36
00:03:46,145 --> 00:03:48,483
Ah. Of course it is.

37
00:03:48,567 --> 00:03:51,489
There's no way Misuzu-san would put fake things on display.

38
00:03:51,823 --> 00:03:54,202
Is that one real too?

39
00:03:58,712 --> 00:04:00,507
It's real. I thought it would be a shame

40
00:04:00,591 --> 00:04:02,302
to keep it locked up in a glass case

41
00:04:02,385 --> 00:04:04,014
all the time.

42
00:04:04,724 --> 00:04:08,732
This is a painting from when we filmed the movie
"Vacation at Rokumeikan"...

43
00:04:08,815 --> 00:04:11,571
but the finished painting didn't have the necklace,

44
00:04:11,655 --> 00:04:13,240
so I thought,

45
00:04:13,324 --> 00:04:14,368
why not?

46
00:04:14,452 --> 00:04:15,579
(Sound) Hmm?

47
00:04:15,663 --> 00:04:17,082
Ah... whoa!

48
00:04:17,165 --> 00:04:20,004
Hey, Dad, be careful.

49
00:04:20,088 --> 00:04:21,173
I know!

50
00:04:21,675 --> 00:04:24,597
(Kogoro panicking) Ah...

51
00:04:24,681 --> 00:04:25,933
Phew...

52
00:04:26,350 --> 00:04:28,354
What are you doing?

53
00:04:28,437 --> 00:04:29,941
Hey, Mama! Hmm?

54
00:04:30,358 --> 00:04:31,695
What is the meaning of this?

55
00:04:31,778 --> 00:04:33,448
What's all this noise?

56
00:04:33,782 --> 00:04:34,826
Why did you cancel

57
00:04:34,909 --> 00:04:36,621
my passing of the audition?

58
00:04:36,705 --> 00:04:39,000
Young lady, please calm down.

59
00:04:39,084 --> 00:04:41,213
I heard it from the production staff.

60
00:04:41,296 --> 00:04:45,054
Mama called and had my passing of the audition cancelled.

61
00:04:45,681 --> 00:04:46,975
Audition?

62
00:04:47,058 --> 00:04:50,566
Saori was trying out for an audition for a movie.

63
00:04:51,066 --> 00:04:55,199
Because, dear... you can't sing, and your acting is terrible.

64
00:04:55,283 --> 00:04:57,663
It would be embarrassing to put you in front of people.

65
00:04:57,747 --> 00:04:58,874
Mother!

66
00:04:58,957 --> 00:05:00,544
Don't decide that on your own!

67
00:05:00,627 --> 00:05:02,130
Be quiet.

68
00:05:02,213 --> 00:05:06,263
I won't let anyone do anything that tarnishes my name.

69
00:05:06,346 --> 00:05:09,186
You being an actress was a long time ago.

70
00:05:09,269 --> 00:05:13,110
Nobody even remembers Shirakawa Misuzu anymore.

71
00:05:13,194 --> 00:05:15,323
Saori. Leave her be.

72
00:05:17,285 --> 00:05:19,749
Now then, let's have lunch.

73
00:05:19,832 --> 00:05:22,713
Yuka, please escort everyone to the terrace.

74
00:05:22,797 --> 00:05:24,341
Yes, ma'am.

75
00:05:35,531 --> 00:05:37,033
Conan-kun, what are you doing?

76
00:05:37,116 --> 00:05:38,578
Coming!

77
00:05:41,918 --> 00:05:43,295
How about some jam?

78
00:05:43,379 --> 00:05:44,590
I'll have some.

79
00:05:45,258 --> 00:05:47,555
I'm sorry about earlier.

80
00:05:47,638 --> 00:05:50,101
When it comes to acting, Mother is still...

81
00:05:50,184 --> 00:05:52,105
strict. No, not at all.

82
00:05:52,565 --> 00:05:55,821
Mother lives in a world of dreams.

83
00:05:55,904 --> 00:05:58,618
The world back when she was a great actress.

84
00:05:58,702 --> 00:06:02,250
Ah... you shouldn't say things like that, Kyosuke-san.

85
00:06:05,381 --> 00:06:08,597
I apologize for earlier, Mouri-san.

86
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:11,184
You had to see such an embarrassing scene.

87
00:06:11,268 --> 00:06:14,065
No, don't worry about it.

88
00:06:14,316 --> 00:06:18,909
Well, no matter how old they get, children are still children.

89
00:06:18,992 --> 00:06:22,791
It's like they say, "A parent's heart is unknown to their child."

90
00:06:23,292 --> 00:06:24,545
Ugh...

91
00:06:27,885 --> 00:06:28,929
Yuka.

92
00:06:29,472 --> 00:06:30,515
Yes?

93
00:06:31,099 --> 00:06:32,143
This isn't the usual

94
00:06:32,226 --> 00:06:34,064
rose jam, is it?

95
00:06:34,147 --> 00:06:35,734
I'm very sorry.

96
00:06:35,817 --> 00:06:37,111
When I checked yesterday,

97
00:06:37,195 --> 00:06:40,577
I thought we had two more bottles in stock.

98
00:06:40,661 --> 00:06:42,038
Go buy some right now.

99
00:06:42,372 --> 00:06:45,754
Mother, you don't have to get that angry over some jam.

100
00:06:45,837 --> 00:06:50,137
At the studio, there was never anyone who forgot what my favorite things were.

101
00:06:50,221 --> 00:06:53,018
That was a long time ago. Wha...

102
00:06:53,102 --> 00:06:56,066
I'm sorry. I'll go buy some right away.

103
00:06:56,818 --> 00:06:58,112
(Door opens)

104
00:06:58,780 --> 00:07:00,157
(Door closes)

105
00:07:02,286 --> 00:07:03,623
Kyosuke.

106
00:07:03,873 --> 00:07:06,546
It's a little early, but it's time for your medicine.

107
00:07:06,629 --> 00:07:08,090
Please get it ready.

108
00:07:08,173 --> 00:07:09,217
Yes.

109
00:07:09,635 --> 00:07:11,889
Well then, Mouri-san, please excuse me.

110
00:07:11,973 --> 00:07:13,727
I'll see you later.

111
00:07:15,187 --> 00:07:16,231
Haah...

112
00:07:16,314 --> 00:07:17,860
(Door closes) I'm sorry.

113
00:07:17,943 --> 00:07:19,905
It's just... No, not at all.

114
00:07:20,281 --> 00:07:24,790
Oh, I'll excuse myself for a moment and go check on Yuka.

115
00:07:24,874 --> 00:07:26,586
Ah, yes.

116
00:07:31,679 --> 00:07:36,229
Haah... What is with this house? (Door opens)

117
00:07:36,313 --> 00:07:38,818
I'm sorry for all the commotion.

118
00:07:38,902 --> 00:07:40,321
Ah, no...

119
00:07:40,404 --> 00:07:41,991
Huh? Chiharu is...

120
00:07:42,366 --> 00:07:45,331
Ah, she went to check on Yuka.

121
00:07:45,414 --> 00:07:46,793
I see.

122
00:07:46,876 --> 00:07:49,965
Hey, is Misuzu-san sick or something?

123
00:07:50,257 --> 00:07:53,807
Huh? Ah, it's a nap.

124
00:07:53,890 --> 00:07:54,934
Huh?

125
00:07:55,017 --> 00:07:57,271
A nap...?

126
00:07:57,481 --> 00:08:00,779
Yes. Every day from 2 to 4 PM,

127
00:08:00,862 --> 00:08:02,533
taking a nap is Mother's daily routine.

128
00:08:02,616 --> 00:08:04,285
She even takes sleeping pills for it.

129
00:08:04,995 --> 00:08:07,584
Apparently it's for her beauty and health.

130
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:16,686
(Brakes screech)

131
00:08:17,061 --> 00:08:18,731
(Crash)

132
00:08:18,815 --> 00:08:24,409
(Horn honking)

133
00:08:25,161 --> 00:08:26,914
Ugh... ugh...

134
00:08:27,123 --> 00:08:29,419
Yuka, are you okay?

135
00:08:31,173 --> 00:08:32,383
What happened?

136
00:08:32,467 --> 00:08:35,849
It's my fault. I wasn't paying attention.

137
00:08:35,932 --> 00:08:38,688
I'm sorry. I was upset...

138
00:08:38,771 --> 00:08:41,819
Oh man... you messed up.

139
00:08:42,111 --> 00:08:43,531
I saw it.

140
00:08:43,615 --> 00:08:47,330
Chiharu-neesan wandered out in front of the car,

141
00:08:47,413 --> 00:08:50,503
and trying to avoid her, the car went plop.

142
00:08:50,587 --> 00:08:52,925
It's not Yuka's fault. (Door opens)

143
00:08:53,008 --> 00:08:54,595
You all! Ah...

144
00:08:55,304 --> 00:08:57,559
What is all this commotion?

145
00:08:57,643 --> 00:08:58,978
Hey, that car...

146
00:08:59,062 --> 00:09:02,611
Please forgive me. It was my carelessness...

147
00:09:02,694 --> 00:09:04,448
No, it was me...

148
00:09:04,823 --> 00:09:06,201
That's enough.

149
00:09:06,284 --> 00:09:10,334
Yuka, as of today, pack your things and leave.

150
00:09:11,253 --> 00:09:12,631
Unbelievable.

151
00:09:12,714 --> 00:09:15,804
Normally, you'd ask something like "Are you hurt?" first.

152
00:09:16,137 --> 00:09:18,893
The car can just be fixed with insurance, right?

153
00:09:18,977 --> 00:09:20,187
That's enough.

154
00:09:20,730 --> 00:09:23,443
Why are you always so selfish, Mama?

155
00:09:23,528 --> 00:09:26,701
Have you ever once thought about how other people feel?

156
00:09:26,951 --> 00:09:30,291
Is that any way to talk to your parent?

157
00:09:30,458 --> 00:09:33,506
I'm tired. I'm going to rest now.

158
00:09:35,301 --> 00:09:37,054
Ugh... ugh...

159
00:09:37,138 --> 00:09:39,225
It's okay, Yuka.

160
00:09:39,309 --> 00:09:41,814
I'll talk to Mother later.

161
00:09:42,356 --> 00:09:44,737
Well then, Mouri-san, please take care of it.

162
00:09:55,090 --> 00:09:57,471
Mouri-san, thank you very much.

163
00:09:57,554 --> 00:10:00,059
Oh, no need to thank me.

164
00:10:00,142 --> 00:10:03,273
My father just stepped on the gas.

165
00:10:06,697 --> 00:10:09,410
Ah, do you smell something burning?

166
00:10:11,081 --> 00:10:13,711
The lady's room is... Mama.

167
00:10:14,087 --> 00:10:15,465
Mother!

168
00:10:17,134 --> 00:10:18,471
Misuzu-san!

169
00:10:21,852 --> 00:10:23,898
Ugh... ugh...

170
00:10:26,027 --> 00:10:27,781
Misuzu-san! Mother!

171
00:10:29,117 --> 00:10:30,578
Kyosuke-kun, grab that side.

172
00:10:30,662 --> 00:10:32,415
Yes. (Coughing)

173
00:10:33,793 --> 00:10:35,003
This is...

174
00:10:41,349 --> 00:10:42,853
Today at around 2 PM,

175
00:10:42,936 --> 00:10:45,650
a fire broke out at the home of actress Shirakawa Misuzu,

176
00:10:45,733 --> 00:10:48,363
and Shirakawa has passed away.

177
00:10:48,823 --> 00:10:51,202
When Mouri-san entered the room,

178
00:10:51,286 --> 00:10:52,914
Shirakawa was already...

179
00:10:52,998 --> 00:10:55,587
Yes. She had taken sleeping pills before going to sleep,

180
00:10:55,670 --> 00:10:58,968
so without noticing the fire,

181
00:10:59,051 --> 00:11:01,974
she must have inhaled a large amount of smoke.

182
00:11:02,057 --> 00:11:03,310
I see.

183
00:11:03,393 --> 00:11:07,318
But the fire started from a strange place.

184
00:11:07,401 --> 00:11:08,613
That's true.

185
00:11:08,696 --> 00:11:10,324
Does your mother smoke?

186
00:11:10,407 --> 00:11:14,958
No. Nobody in this house smokes, not just Mother.

187
00:11:18,674 --> 00:11:20,010
This is...

188
00:11:22,097 --> 00:11:23,266
Could it be...

189
00:11:26,774 --> 00:11:28,653
That's it.

190
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:31,992
...Which means this is a murder case.

191
00:11:32,076 --> 00:11:34,038
And the culprit is...

192
00:11:39,716 --> 00:11:42,346
The culprit is that person.

193
00:11:53,227 --> 00:11:54,354
Well then.

194
00:11:54,896 --> 00:11:56,692
The sun is setting,

195
00:11:56,775 --> 00:12:00,116
and since we can't determine whether it's an incident or an accident,

196
00:12:00,199 --> 00:12:02,787
we'll head back to the station and wait for the forensics results...

197
00:12:02,871 --> 00:12:05,126
Wait, please, Tamagawa-keiji.

198
00:12:05,209 --> 00:12:06,795
Huh? Huh?

199
00:12:07,088 --> 00:12:08,507
Is there a problem?

200
00:12:08,591 --> 00:12:09,801
Ah, no, no.

201
00:12:09,885 --> 00:12:12,098
(Tranquilizer dart hits) Ah! Whoa!

202
00:12:12,182 --> 00:12:14,769
Dad? Mo... Mouri-san?

203
00:12:14,853 --> 00:12:17,692
Could this be the Sleeping Kogoro?

204
00:12:17,775 --> 00:12:19,654
What? Everyone.

205
00:12:19,738 --> 00:12:21,033
This fire was intentionally set

206
00:12:21,116 --> 00:12:25,333
to murder Shirakawa Misuzu-san.

207
00:12:25,416 --> 00:12:26,418
Huh...

208
00:12:26,752 --> 00:12:29,090
Are you saying this is a murder case?

209
00:12:29,507 --> 00:12:33,265
That's right. And the culprit is among us.

210
00:12:33,349 --> 00:12:34,726
Huh?

211
00:12:35,770 --> 00:12:37,190
But, Dad,

212
00:12:37,273 --> 00:12:40,238
everyone was by the pond at that time.

213
00:12:40,321 --> 00:12:44,120
Ah, probably a type of convergent fire.

214
00:12:44,204 --> 00:12:46,625
Hmm... convergent fire?

215
00:12:47,085 --> 00:12:51,468
A convergent fire is a fire caused by water in a plastic bottle or something

216
00:12:51,551 --> 00:12:55,059
acting as a convex lens.

217
00:12:56,520 --> 00:12:58,148
In other words, Mouri-san,

218
00:12:58,232 --> 00:13:01,113
sunlight was concentrated on the surface of that painting

219
00:13:01,196 --> 00:13:03,158
and ignited it...?

220
00:13:03,242 --> 00:13:08,043
But this room faces north. Sunlight doesn't come in.

221
00:13:08,127 --> 00:13:09,796
Please look outside the window.

222
00:13:09,879 --> 00:13:10,923
Huh?

223
00:13:11,216 --> 00:13:14,055
That building with glass windows

224
00:13:14,139 --> 00:13:15,725
that looks like it was cut diagonally with a knife.

225
00:13:15,808 --> 00:13:19,774
Does seeing that remind you of anything, Kyosuke-san?

226
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:22,905
That's right.

227
00:13:22,989 --> 00:13:26,038
When I rushed into this room...

228
00:13:27,540 --> 00:13:31,256
But even if sunlight reflected off that building,

229
00:13:31,340 --> 00:13:34,763
it would just hit the opposite wall... Ah!

230
00:13:35,598 --> 00:13:36,850
A mirror!

231
00:13:36,933 --> 00:13:40,775
No, even if it reflected off that mirror,

232
00:13:40,858 --> 00:13:44,157
I still don't think the light would hit the portrait.

233
00:13:47,413 --> 00:13:49,459
That does seem unlikely.

234
00:13:49,542 --> 00:13:51,671
Then let's verify it.

235
00:13:53,675 --> 00:13:55,054
Like this?

236
00:13:55,137 --> 00:13:56,848
A little higher.

237
00:13:56,932 --> 00:13:58,060
This much?

238
00:13:58,143 --> 00:13:59,187
Okay.

239
00:13:59,270 --> 00:14:01,191
Now, please turn on the switch.

240
00:14:05,241 --> 00:14:06,576
Just as I thought.

241
00:14:06,660 --> 00:14:10,584
The light went to the wall opposite the painting.

242
00:14:10,876 --> 00:14:12,296
Now, Yuka-san.

243
00:14:12,380 --> 00:14:15,803
Please return the mirror on the floor to its original position.

244
00:14:15,886 --> 00:14:17,056
Okay.

245
00:14:17,348 --> 00:14:21,273
It probably fell during the commotion of the firefighting efforts.

246
00:14:21,731 --> 00:14:24,988
Can you see the marks carved into the base?

247
00:14:25,239 --> 00:14:28,036
Um... Ah, there they are.

248
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:30,499
There are also marks on the glass case,

249
00:14:30,583 --> 00:14:33,046
so please align them with those.

250
00:14:33,130 --> 00:14:34,174
Yes.

251
00:14:37,597 --> 00:14:39,642
Please also adjust the vertical angle.

252
00:14:39,726 --> 00:14:41,021
Yes.

253
00:14:43,066 --> 00:14:45,446
Oh! The light is hitting the painting!

254
00:14:45,821 --> 00:14:47,950
Please do the other two as well.

255
00:14:55,674 --> 00:14:56,843
Oh!

256
00:14:56,927 --> 00:14:59,224
Here's how it works.

257
00:14:59,849 --> 00:15:02,688
The light reflected off the glass building

258
00:15:02,772 --> 00:15:05,861
passes through the window and reflects off the full-length mirror on the wall,

259
00:15:05,945 --> 00:15:10,287
then reflects off the three mirrors on top of the glass case,

260
00:15:10,371 --> 00:15:12,875
and concentrated on a single point on the painting.

261
00:15:13,502 --> 00:15:15,172
The culprit likely

262
00:15:15,256 --> 00:15:18,387
meticulously determined the positions of the mirrors in advance.

263
00:15:19,180 --> 00:15:21,685
But please remember.

264
00:15:21,768 --> 00:15:24,107
When I was guided here before noon,

265
00:15:24,190 --> 00:15:26,903
I accidentally knocked over a mirror.

266
00:15:27,405 --> 00:15:28,448
In other words,

267
00:15:28,532 --> 00:15:33,166
there's a high chance they were misaligned from the positions the culprit had set.

268
00:15:33,250 --> 00:15:34,669
And yet,

269
00:15:34,752 --> 00:15:38,427
the fire occurred exactly as the culprit intended.

270
00:15:38,510 --> 00:15:39,679
That means...

271
00:15:39,762 --> 00:15:43,812
Ah! That means the culprit readjusted the positions of the mirrors!

272
00:15:44,063 --> 00:15:45,065
Yes.

273
00:15:45,149 --> 00:15:48,238
And there is only one person who could have done that.

274
00:15:48,614 --> 00:15:51,828
The one who slipped past us as we headed to the terrace

275
00:15:51,911 --> 00:15:55,294
and remained in this room—Shirakawa Chiharu-san.

276
00:15:57,506 --> 00:15:59,677
It can only be you.

277
00:16:00,554 --> 00:16:01,806
That's...

278
00:16:01,890 --> 00:16:02,975
No way...

279
00:16:03,810 --> 00:16:07,193
Is it true, Chiharu? You killed Mother?

280
00:16:07,818 --> 00:16:10,407
No, wait a moment.

281
00:16:10,491 --> 00:16:14,165
Mother only had the window open for about two or three minutes.

282
00:16:14,248 --> 00:16:18,173
Can a fire source really be created in such a short time?

283
00:16:18,256 --> 00:16:19,884
Yes, it can.

284
00:16:20,469 --> 00:16:23,892
Chiharu-san, after adjusting the mirrors,

285
00:16:23,975 --> 00:16:26,731
didn't you apply a chemical to the painting that ignites easily...

286
00:16:26,815 --> 00:16:30,800
probably a thinning agent used when painting with oils?

287
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:32,100
Thinning agent?

288
00:16:32,283 --> 00:16:32,910
Yes.

289
00:16:33,078 --> 00:16:37,920
Volatile solvents like turpentine and petroleum

290
00:16:38,003 --> 00:16:40,926
have flash points below 50 degrees Celsius.

291
00:16:42,888 --> 00:16:45,769
You were also the one who hid the rose jam, weren't you?

292
00:16:46,146 --> 00:16:50,779
Just as you planned, Misuzu-san sent Yuka out to buy new jam.

293
00:16:51,197 --> 00:16:55,289
And then you ran out in front of Yuka's car...

294
00:16:56,082 --> 00:16:57,418
Ah!

295
00:16:57,877 --> 00:16:59,922
(Crash)

296
00:17:05,851 --> 00:17:07,313
You all!

297
00:17:07,772 --> 00:17:09,901
What is all this commotion?

298
00:17:09,984 --> 00:17:11,321
Hey, that car...

299
00:17:11,404 --> 00:17:14,494
Have you ever once thought about how other people feel?

300
00:17:14,577 --> 00:17:17,333
Is that any way to talk to your parent?

301
00:17:20,172 --> 00:17:22,343
Is that true, Chiharu?

302
00:17:24,305 --> 00:17:27,978
Is it true, sis? Chiharu-neesan killed Mama?

303
00:17:28,063 --> 00:17:29,524
Evidence? Huh?

304
00:17:30,067 --> 00:17:32,196
If you're going to go that far, Mouri-san,

305
00:17:32,279 --> 00:17:34,617
then you'll have to show me proper evidence.

306
00:17:34,700 --> 00:17:36,538
Evidence?

307
00:17:36,621 --> 00:17:40,796
Yes. Everything you've said so far has just been speculation.

308
00:17:41,422 --> 00:17:43,969
Just because I was the last to leave the room,

309
00:17:44,053 --> 00:17:47,643
does that prove that I adjusted the mirrors?

310
00:17:47,893 --> 00:17:48,937
Ridiculous.

311
00:17:49,021 --> 00:17:50,065
Yuka-san.

312
00:17:50,357 --> 00:17:51,901
Ah, yes.

313
00:17:52,361 --> 00:17:55,367
There were lilies arranged in this room, weren't there?

314
00:17:55,450 --> 00:17:58,582
Yes. Because the lady loved them.

315
00:17:58,915 --> 00:18:00,836
And in the other rooms?

316
00:18:00,919 --> 00:18:03,758
No, the only room that had lilies arranged

317
00:18:03,842 --> 00:18:05,554
was this one.

318
00:18:05,637 --> 00:18:09,103
Excuse me, Mouri-san, what exactly are you talking about?

319
00:18:09,604 --> 00:18:11,858
About the evidence, of course.

320
00:18:11,941 --> 00:18:13,111
Huh?

321
00:18:13,403 --> 00:18:14,614
In other words,

322
00:18:14,697 --> 00:18:17,870
I'm talking about the lily pollen

323
00:18:18,413 --> 00:18:20,500
on the outside of your right sleeve.

324
00:18:20,584 --> 00:18:21,628
Ha...

325
00:18:28,767 --> 00:18:31,272
And what is that supposed to prove?

326
00:18:31,940 --> 00:18:35,238
Why is pollen from lilies,

327
00:18:35,322 --> 00:18:38,286
which were only arranged in this room,

328
00:18:38,370 --> 00:18:42,336
on your right sleeve?

329
00:18:42,419 --> 00:18:43,421
That's... I must have touched the lilies somehow.

330
00:18:43,505 --> 00:18:45,217
So then...

331
00:18:45,676 --> 00:18:47,513
I don't remember something like that!

332
00:18:47,888 --> 00:18:49,892
Please think carefully.

333
00:18:50,143 --> 00:18:54,318
The lilies were in a vase on top of the glass case.

334
00:18:55,404 --> 00:18:58,660
Pollen on the outside of your right sleeve means

335
00:18:58,743 --> 00:19:02,459
that you reached out your right hand to the left side of the lilies

336
00:19:02,543 --> 00:19:05,340
and performed some kind of task.

337
00:19:06,217 --> 00:19:08,346
So what was there?

338
00:19:09,974 --> 00:19:13,732
Yes. There were the mirrors

339
00:19:13,815 --> 00:19:17,364
used in the earlier experiment

340
00:19:17,781 --> 00:19:19,744
to reflect and concentrate the light.

341
00:19:20,954 --> 00:19:22,624
Ah...

342
00:19:24,378 --> 00:19:25,505
Chiharu...

343
00:19:25,589 --> 00:19:29,346
Chiharu-neesan, why? Why did you do that to Mama?

344
00:19:29,430 --> 00:19:31,392
"Chiharu-san." Huh?

345
00:19:31,976 --> 00:19:35,233
No matter how much time passed, she always called me

346
00:19:35,317 --> 00:19:37,279
"Chiharu-san."

347
00:19:37,362 --> 00:19:41,204
Even though she called you all "Kyosuke" and "Saori."

348
00:19:41,287 --> 00:19:43,625
Just because of that? Hmph.

349
00:19:44,919 --> 00:19:48,635
Mouri-san, I'm my father's stepchild.

350
00:19:49,261 --> 00:19:52,059
When I heard that Father was going to remarry her,

351
00:19:52,142 --> 00:19:53,770
I was very happy.

352
00:19:54,563 --> 00:19:57,986
After all, she was a great actress I admired.

353
00:19:58,196 --> 00:20:01,369
So I tried my best to get her to like me.

354
00:20:01,619 --> 00:20:03,915
I never said anything selfish,

355
00:20:03,998 --> 00:20:06,671
and I willingly helped around the house.

356
00:20:07,089 --> 00:20:09,802
But what came back from her was always...

357
00:20:09,885 --> 00:20:12,014
"Well done, Chiharu-san."

358
00:20:12,099 --> 00:20:15,939
"Thank you, Chiharu-san."
"No, Chiharu-san."

359
00:20:16,023 --> 00:20:18,695
Chiharu-san, Chiharu-san, Chiharu-san...

360
00:20:23,746 --> 00:20:25,458
It was last week.

361
00:20:26,502 --> 00:20:29,884
Ah, that girl doesn't matter.

362
00:20:31,345 --> 00:20:32,514
It's fine, it's fine.

363
00:20:32,598 --> 00:20:35,270
After all, that girl is just my husband's stepchild.

364
00:20:36,981 --> 00:20:40,989
Yes, that's right. The only children who carry Shirakawa Misuzu's blood

365
00:20:41,073 --> 00:20:43,536
are Kyosuke and Saori.

366
00:20:43,912 --> 00:20:48,796
And I won't give a single yen of my fortune to anyone else.

367
00:20:48,880 --> 00:20:50,050
Hohohoho...

368
00:20:50,133 --> 00:20:53,556
Ugh... Hohohoho...

369
00:20:55,644 --> 00:20:56,896
Chiharu-san.

370
00:20:57,648 --> 00:21:00,445
This is just my personal opinion, but...

371
00:21:00,820 --> 00:21:04,370
don't you think you tried too hard?

372
00:21:04,662 --> 00:21:05,872
Ha...

373
00:21:06,207 --> 00:21:09,463
A parent-child relationship isn't something you become by trying hard.

374
00:21:09,546 --> 00:21:12,009
You probably could have been a little more selfish

375
00:21:12,094 --> 00:21:13,888
as well.

376
00:21:14,223 --> 00:21:15,892
From the very beginning,

377
00:21:15,976 --> 00:21:18,398
you started off on the wrong foot.

378
00:21:20,443 --> 00:21:23,408
Ugh... ugh...

379
00:21:23,491 --> 00:21:29,503
(Crying)

380
00:21:32,175 --> 00:21:38,187
♪~♪

381
00:22:46,073 --> 00:22:51,834
♪~♪

382
00:22:53,087 --> 00:22:54,840
Hey, Dad?

383
00:22:55,258 --> 00:22:58,181
Huh? You went horse racing again, didn't you?

384
00:22:58,473 --> 00:23:01,437
D... don't be stupid. There's no way that's true.

385
00:23:01,729 --> 00:23:04,985
...Geez. And on top of that, you even ate curry,

386
00:23:05,069 --> 00:23:06,489
so what am I supposed to do about dinner?

387
00:23:06,572 --> 00:23:08,659
Huh? Wh... how did you...

388
00:23:09,328 --> 00:23:11,874
Hmm... It's on your shirt.

389
00:23:11,957 --> 00:23:14,003
A curry stain.

390
00:23:14,671 --> 00:23:18,596
Ah, no... Ahahaha... (Clears throat)

391
00:23:18,679 --> 00:23:20,558
Okay, I admit I ate curry.

392
00:23:20,642 --> 00:23:22,854
But I didn't eat it at the racetrack...

393
00:23:22,938 --> 00:23:24,858
Uncle. Hmm?

394
00:23:24,942 --> 00:23:26,195
Your ear, your ear.

395
00:23:26,278 --> 00:23:27,614
Ah!

396
00:23:28,574 --> 00:23:32,791
Ah, huh? How did this thing get in my ear...

397
00:23:32,874 --> 00:23:35,505
That's strange. Strange things do happen.

398
00:23:35,588 --> 00:23:39,346
You're a sore loser. Allowance, 50% cut.

399
00:23:39,429 --> 00:23:42,394
Huh? Ahaha... hee...

400
00:23:42,477 --> 00:23:45,650
Your Honor! Oh, such injustice...

401
00:23:46,110 --> 00:23:48,322
Haha. You're a detective,

402
00:23:48,406 --> 00:23:50,451
so pay attention to the little details.

403
00:23:53,541 --> 00:23:55,878
One stab in the chest with a blade, huh?

404
00:23:56,463 --> 00:23:58,509
Did Kitajima-san do it?

405
00:23:58,593 --> 00:24:00,388
Wasn't it Hiroto-san?

406
00:24:00,471 --> 00:24:01,473
Huh?

407
00:24:01,557 --> 00:24:05,690
I wondered who it was, but it's Hiroto-san. And Morishita-san too.

408
00:24:05,773 --> 00:24:08,404
You two are the culprits, aren't you? Huh?

409
00:24:08,654 --> 00:24:12,954
There's one natural thing of the same color in this room.

410
00:24:13,039 --> 00:24:14,666
Everyone, which one is it?

411
00:24:15,126 --> 00:24:16,420
That one! That one!

412
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:18,549
Next Conan...

413
00:24:18,549 --> 00:24:22,549
"The Figure That Was Too Good"

414
00:24:37,725 --> 00:24:40,063
Next Conan's Hint.

415
00:24:40,063 --> 00:24:42,063
"Paint"

416
00:24:42,359 --> 00:24:43,821
Are you going horse racing again?

417
00:24:43,904 --> 00:24:44,948
Because it's the Year of the Horse.

418
00:24:45,031 --> 00:24:46,827
A clever excuse.
